    {
      "parameters": {
        "assignments": {
          "assignments": [
            {
              "id": "a1",
              "name": "text",
              "value": "LEAVE POLICY: Annual leave - 20 working days per year. Sick leave - 10 days per year, medical certificate required for absences of 3 or more consecutive days. Maternity leave - 16 weeks fully paid for primary caregivers. Paternity leave - 2 weeks fully paid. Emergency/bereavement leave - up to 3 days for immediate family. All leave requests must be submitted at least 5 business days in advance through the HR portal.\n\nREMOTE WORK POLICY: Employees may work remotely up to 3 days per week with manager approval. Standard working hours 9AM-5PM must be maintained unless agreed otherwise. Home office setup expenses up to $500 are reimbursable annually. All remote work must comply with data security guidelines.\n\nPERFORMANCE REVIEW PROCESS: Bi-annual performance reviews conducted in June and December. Written performance plan provided at the start of each year. Rating scale: Exceeds Expectations, Meets Expectations, Needs Improvement, Unsatisfactory. Salary adjustments are linked to year-end performance reviews. Employees may appeal ratings within 10 business days.\n\nCOMPENSATION AND BENEFITS: Annual salary reviews each January. Full health insurance for the employee; 50% for dependents. 401k plan with 4% company match. EAP available 24/7. Annual wellness stipend of $300. Professional development budget of $1,500 per year.\n\nONBOARDING AND OFFBOARDING: New employees have a 90-day probationary period. Onboarding includes 1-week orientation plus role-specific training. Notice period: 2 weeks for employees, 4 weeks for managers. HR conducts exit interviews for all departing employees.\n\nWORKPLACE CONDUCT: Zero tolerance for harassment, discrimination, or bullying. Business casual dress code; formal attire for client meetings. Zero tolerance for alcohol and drugs during working hours. Confidentiality agreements must be maintained even after employment ends. No company-related social media posts without HR approval.\n\nIT AND SECURITY: Work devices must not be used for personal activities. VPN required for all remote access. Passwords must be changed every 90 days. Report security incidents to it@company.com. Personal devices may only access company email via approved apps.\n\nPAYROLL: Salaries paid bi-weekly on Fridays. Timesheets due by noon on last Thursday of each pay period. Overtime compensated at 1.5x regular hourly rate. Expense reimbursements processed within 10 business days.",
              "type": "string"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
